    "26455236": {
      "title": "Paxillin and focal adhesion signalling",
      "abstract": "To facilitate a rapid response to environmental change, cells use scaffolding — or adaptor — proteins to recruit key components of their signal-transduction machinery to specific subcellular locations. Paxillin is a multi-domain adaptor found at the interface between the plasma membrane and the actin cytoskeleton. Here it provides a platform for the integration and processing of adhesion- and growth factor-related signals."
